}}

=== Titles and styles ===
*'''29 October 1875&nbsp;<U+2013> 10 January 1893''': ''Her Royal Highness'' Princess Marie of Edinburgh, Princess of Saxe-Coburg and Gotha, Duchess of Saxony{{sfn|Eilers|1987|p=189}}<ref>{{London Gazette|issue=25495|startpage=3531|date=28 July 1885}} {{London Gazette|issue=26184|startpage=3865|date=20 July 1891}}</ref>
*'''10 January 1893&nbsp;<U+2013> 10 October 1914''': ''Her Royal Highness'' The Crown Princess of Romania<ref>{{London Gazette|issue=27489|supp=yes|startpage=6860|date=28 October 1902}}</ref>
*'''10 October 1914&nbsp;<U+2013> 20 July 1927''': ''Her Majesty'' The Queen of Romania
*'''20 July 1927&nbsp;<U+2013> 18 July 1938''': ''Her Majesty'' Queen Marie of Romania

=== British arms ===
As a male-line grandchild of a British Sovereign, Marie bore the arms of the kingdom, with an [[inescutcheon]] for Saxony, differenced by a five-point label argent, the outer pair of which bore anchors azure, the inner roses gules, and the central a cross gules. In 1917, the inescutcheon was dropped by Royal Warrant from George V.<ref>[http://www.heraldica.org/topics/britain/cadency.htm Heraldica <U+2013> British Royalty Cadency]</ref>

=== Honours ===
Marie was a recipient of the following national and foreign honours:
* [[Image:Ro1ocr.gif|50px|link=]] Grand Cross of the [[Order of the Crown (Romania)|Order of the Crown]] (Romania){{sfn|Elsberry|1972|p=147}}
* [[Image:Legion Honneur Chevalier ribbon.svg|50px|link=]] ''[[Legion d'Honneur]]'' (France){{sfn|Mandache|2011|p=41}}
* [[Image:Medaille militaire ribbon.svg|50px|link=]] ''[[M<U+00E9>daille militaire]]'' (France){{sfn|Marghiloman|1927|p=131}}
* [[Image:Cavaliere OCI BAR.svg|50px|link=]] Dame of the [[Order of the Crown of Italy|Order of the Crown]] (Italy){{sfn|Marghiloman|1927|p=199}}
* [[Image:ImperialOrderCrownIndiaRibbon .gif|50px|link=]] Dame of the [[Order of the Crown of India|Order of the Crown]] (India)<ref name="ordersuk">{{cite web | title =Prince Alfred | work =Land Forces of Britain, The Empire and The Commonwealth | publisher =[www.regiments.org Regiments.org] | year =2007 | url =http://www.regiments.org/biography/royals/1844alfr.htm | accessdate = 2007-12-30 |archiveurl = http://web.archive.org/web/20071013160929/http://www.regiments.org/biography/royals/1844alfr.htm <!-- Bot retrieved archive --> |archivedate = 16 November 2007}}</ref>
* [[Image:Royal Red Cross (UK) ribbon.png|50px|link=]] Dame of the [[Royal Red Cross]] (United Kingdom)<ref name="ordersuk" />
* [[Image:Royal Order of Victoria and Albert - ribbon bar.gif|50px|link=]] Dame of the [[Royal Order of Victoria and Albert]] (United Kingdom)<ref name="ordersuk" />
* [[Image:Order of St John (UK) ribbon.png|50px|link=]] Dame of Justice of the [[Venerable Order of Saint John|Venerable Order of Saint John of Jerusalem]] (United Kingdom)<ref name="ordersuk" />
* [[Image:Order of Queen Maria Luisa (Spain) - ribbon bar.png|50px|link=]] 1,007th Dame of the Royal [[Order of Queen Maria Luisa]] (Spain)<ref>[http://www.geneall.net/U/tit_page.php?id=25500 GeneAll.net <U+2013> Damas de la Real Orden de la Reina Mar<U+00ED>a Luisa<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>

